No fewer than 500 persons have benefited from the financial support offered by a Non-Governmental Organization (NGO), the Possibility Specialist Foundation, rendering assistance to the less privileged people in the society. The founder, Mr. Egona Abraham, while speaking with journalists in Akure yesterday, said the organization is determined to raising and assisting people in a bid to help realize their dreams. Abraham added that various humanitarian services are also rendered by the organization for the good of the masses and the benefit of mankind. He recounted that the organization engages in different schemes which provide an opportunity for subscribers to enjoy various dividends, including loans and provision of basic needs. Abraham, who stressed that the organization is not into Ponzi nor referral scheme, maintained that the major aim of the organization was to cater to the financial needs of the less privileged in the society. He said the organization also engages in empowerment programme to boost the living condition of its members, adding that the organization operates on high-level financial intelligence and discipline. Speaking on the sustainability plans, he noted that other items including foodstuff, electronics and cars among others were being donated by individuals who subscribe to the policy of the organization. To curtail fraud, he hinted that the organization is monitored by anti-graft agencies, especially the Economic and Financial Crimes Commission (EFCC) and is certified by the Special Control Unit against Money Laundering (SCUML). According to him, “Our organization is registered with the Corporate Affairs Commission (CAC) with presence all over Nigeria and major countries of the world. “We join hands with the government in making life comfortable for the masses especially through skill acquisition training and empowerment offers.”  To enable commenting and other interactive features, please switch to the more advanced .